</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Paediatric pads and devices</strong> - When available, use paediatric pads for children under 8 years or weighing less than 25kg. If paediatric pads are unavailable, it is generally considered safe to use adult pads, placing one in the middle of the child’s chest and the other on the back.




































